{
  "id": "c0c0c0c0-0023-0000-0000-000000000000",
  "name": "Error Handling",
  "type": "871ae771-b9b1-4f40-8c7f-d9038bfb69c3",
  "created": 1738454400000,
  "modified": 1775756670985,
  "content": {
    "description": [
      ":doc",
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "Hobson uses a three-tier error handling system that keeps the kernel minimal while allowing userland code to provide rich error experiences."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "Three Tiers"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h3",
        {
          "s": "Tier 1: Kernel Event Emission"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "The kernel catches errors and emits a "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "error-event"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " event:"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":code-block",
        {
          "s": "async captureError(error, context = {}) {\n  this.events.emit({\n    type: EVENT_IDS.SYSTEM_ERROR,\n    content: { error, context, timestamp: Date.now() }\n  });\n}"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "The kernel does NOT create error items, show UI, or decide how to present errors. It just announces that an error happened."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h3",
        {
          "s": "Tier 2: Userland Error Handler"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "The "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "default-error-handler"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " library subscribes to "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "error-event"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " via "
        },
        [
          ":item-ref",
          {
            "s": "c0c0c0c0-0006-0000-0000-000000000000"
          },
          {
            "s": "declarative watches"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": ":"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":code-block",
        {
          "s": "// In default-error-handler item\ncontent: {\n  watches: [{ event: \"error-event\" }],\n  code: `\n    export async function onErrorEvent(event, api) {\n      // Create an error item for persistent record\n      const errorItem = {\n        id: crypto.randomUUID(),\n        type: ERROR_TYPE_ID,\n        content: {\n          message: event.content.error.message,\n          stack: event.content.error.stack,\n          context: event.content.context,\n          timestamp: event.content.timestamp\n        }\n      };\n      await api.set(errorItem);\n      // Show toast notification\n      showErrorToast(errorItem);\n    }\n  `\n}"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "This is a regular userland library — inspectable, modifiable, replaceable."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h3",
        {
          "s": "Tier 3: Fallback (Emergency REPL)"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "If the error handler itself fails, or if errors occur before boot completes:"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":ol",
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            {
              "s": "Kernel tries to load "
            },
            [
              ":code",
              {
                "s": "repl-ui"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " directly via "
            },
            [
              ":code",
              {
                "s": "require()"
              }
            ]
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            {
              "s": "If available, calls "
            },
            [
              ":code",
              {
                "s": "replLib.showEmergency(error, context)"
              }
            ]
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            {
              "s": "If REPL is also broken → errors go to browser DevTools console"
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            {
              "s": "Last resort → "
            },
            [
              ":item-ref",
              {
                "s": "33333333-7777-0000-0000-000000000000"
              },
              {
                "s": "safe mode"
              }
            ]
          ]
        ]
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "Error Item Structure"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "Error items persist error information for later review:"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":code-block",
        {
          "s": "{\n  type: \"error-type-uuid\",\n  content: {\n    message: \"Cannot read property 'name' of undefined\",\n    stack: \"at render (blob:...:42:15)\\n  at ...\",\n    context: { itemId: \"...\", viewId: \"...\" },\n    timestamp: 1706000000000\n  }\n}"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h3",
        {
          "s": "Stack Trace Parsing"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "The error view parses stack traces to identify item references. Blob URLs contain item IDs, which are extracted to create navigable frames:"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":code-block",
        {
          "s": "at render (blob:https://hobson.app/f1111111-0008-0000-0000-000000000000:42:15)\n→ kernel:rendering-system, line 42"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "Clicking a frame navigates to the source item."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "Error Views"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":ul",
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            [
              ":strong",
              {
                "s": "Error view"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " — displays a single error with parsed stack trace and navigable frames"
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            [
              ":strong",
              {
                "s": "Error list view"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " — displays recent errors in a list, useful as a dashboard widget"
            }
          ]
        ]
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "Design Rationale"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h3",
        {
          "s": "Why Extensible?"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "Users might want different error handling: logging to a file, sending to a webhook, auto-creating bug items. Making the handler a replaceable item enables all of these."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h3",
        {
          "s": "Why User-Controlled?"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "The kernel doesn't know how to present errors well. UI decisions (toast vs modal vs inline) belong in userland where they can use views, styling, and user preferences."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h3",
        {
          "s": "Why Kernel Minimal?"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "The kernel only emits events. This means:"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":ul",
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            {
              "s": "No error UI code in the kernel to break"
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            {
              "s": "Error handling can be upgraded without touching the kernel"
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            {
              "s": "The kernel itself can never be broken by error handling bugs"
            }
          ]
        ]
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "See Also"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":ul",
        [
          ":li",
